The paper deals with secure communication in wireless networks, which falls under the scope of information theory (cs.IT) and network security (cs.NI). The use of social relationships among network nodes also suggests a potential overlap with social networks (cs.SI) and system and control theory (cs.SY). Finally, the proposed jamming scheme involves interference management, which is a common topic in cryptography and security (cs.CR).
